# 8. ステージを笑顔に

Emu: That's the schedule we currently have leading up to our next show!
Sakurako: Thank you for that. I didn't see any major problems.
Sakurako: However, considering the show's story, we may want to work out how to use the stage devices sooner rather than later...
Emu: Right! The director also told me about some things that he wants to try out...
Emu: So, I believe we should consider bringing in some new equipment for this show!
Emu: We'll have to figure out how to work that into our budget...
Emu: But I plan on doing everything I can to make sure our show makes all the guests smile!
Sakurako: I see. If discussions with the staff are coming along, then it sounds like we have nothing to worry about...
Sakurako: That just leaves you having to talk to our stage manager.
Sakurako: Anyway, Otori, I'm counting on you...
Emu: Yes, I promise to do my best!
Emu: (Hehe☆ Sakurako said she's counting on me!)
Emu: (She was so worried when I first told her that I'd be running things...)
Emu: (But it feels like I'm slowly gaining her trust.)
Emu: No, I can't let my guard down and start acting all loosey-goosey!
Emu: I still have a lot of meetings left at the other stages, so I have to keep doing my best...!
Emu: I need to do everything I can since Keisuke and Shosuke gave me this opportunity to run Phoenix Wonderland's stages!
Emu: A-Are you sure...?!
Emu: You guys are really gonna let me run the stages at Phoenix Wonderland...?
Shosuke: Yes, but it's not like we're going to immediately let you run everything. It'll be a step-by-step process.
Keisuke: Obviously, we still have the final say and bear ultimate responsibility... But some experience running stages should benefit you in the future.
Emu: My future...
Shosuke: Ever since your friends left Phoenix Wonderland, you've been following us around and saying, “I wanna learn more about management and stuff”...
Shosuke: Shadowing someone is one way to learn, but experiencing what actually happens on the ground is also important for operators and managers.
Shosuke: And you have an incredibly creative mind. As the park's operators, we're happy to make use of such an asset.
Keisuke: Exactly. We think we can trust you with this, provided you have the drive. So, what do you say...?
Emu: Yeah! I wanna do it!
Emu: I wanna learn as much as I can about management to help make my dream come true!
Shosuke: To make your dream come true... Yes, we had a feeling you'd say that.
Emu: Hehe... I actually made a really important realization while watching you guys work.
Emu: I honestly didn't know just how much thought and effort went into getting someone else to smile and laugh.
Emu: I thought I knew how hard that was... But I realize now that my understanding was poor.
Keisuke: Emu...
Emu: So, I wanna do this...
Emu: In order to make people all around the world smile, I'll start by filling the stages at Phoenix Wonderland with lots and lots of joy...!
Keisuke: We understand how you feel. So, we'll do what we can on our end.
Keisuke: Again, we'll still have final say on what happens in the park. So, you should come up with ideas for making everybody smile the way you always do.
Emu: Okay, I will!
Emu: Hehe. I'm gonna let the others know right away...!
Shosuke: You mean Tenma and them?
Emu: Yup! They're all working super hard towards making their dreams come true, so I wanna tell them that I'm doing the same!
Keisuke: I see... I take it that means they're each doing well in their new environments?
Emu: They are!
Emu: Anyway, Keisuke, Shosuke...
Emu: Thanks for doing all this for me!
Emu: I promise to do my very best!
Keisuke: Yes, we'll be expecting good results...
Keisuke: Towards making their dreams come true, huh...?
Shosuke: They're still high schoolers, so I feel like they should be stopping to smell the flowers a little more.
Shosuke: Even when they decided to disband their troupe, they didn't come ask for our advice until everything was basically set in stone.
Keisuke: True...
Keisuke: In any case, we should support Emu however we can when it comes to giving her opportunities to learn more about business management.
Keisuke: Since that should help her make her dream a reality.
Shosuke: Yes, I agree...
Staff Member: Alright, let's go with the budget and casting plan we outlined during the meeting we just had...
Emu: Okay! I'll come up with a schedule for auditions to fill out the cast and let you know once it's finished!
Staff Member: Understood. Then, I'll be waiting to hear from you.
Emu: (Hehe. I'm almost done with the stage inspections and meetings I had scheduled!)
Emu: (All that's left is the Wonder Stage. They should be doing a show right now...)
Emu: Alright, in that case...
Big Bear: *Sob* “Everybody keeps running away because they're so scared of me...”
Big Bear: “But I guess that's natural since I look so big and scary... I'm never going to be able to make any friends...”
Boy: “That's not true. I'm sure everyone will become your friends once they understand what you're really like. I mean, I've never met someone kinder than you! Also...”
Boy: “At the very least, I consider you my friend.”
Emu: (They're all sparkling today too... In particular...)
Emu: (The boy playing the protagonist, Shiratori, has really been on a roll lately☆ I know he's been practicing a lot...!)
Children: The guy playing the main character's so cool!
Audience: I'm actually a huge fan of his. I've gotta get more great pictures of him today!
Boy: “Don't worry! They might be crying or feeling angry now, but I know a way to get them to become your friends.”
Boy: “You just need to do a happy dance for them!”
Boy: “Come on, everyone, join us! You can even take the hands of the people next to you!”
Children: Oh, that sounds like fun...! Let's try, Dad!
Audience: This is a little embarrassing... But, umm... Like this?
Emu: (Wow...! They look like they're all having so much fun☆)
Emu: (The kids and the grown-ups. Their eyes are all sparkling.)
Emu: (The crowd and everybody on stage are all smiling!)
Emu: (This is so great...)
Emu: (This reminds me of when we...)
Emu: ...
Emu: I have to keep at it...
Emu: (Tsukasa and the others played a huge role in saving this place. So...)
Emu: (Moving forward, I have to do absolutely everything I can to keep it going...!)
Emu: (Especially with how hard the new troupe here is working...)
Emu: (I'm going to fill this park with smiles and laughter that spreads out to the entire world...)
Emu: (I've gotta keep doing more and more to make that happen.)
Emu: Nice work, everyone☆ You guys put on another super duper wonderhoy performance today!
Wonder Stage Cast Member A: Hello, Ms. Otori. We didn't realize that you were watching!
Emu: Yup! I was actually dancing along with you guys backstage towards the end there!
Emu: I really wish I could see you all perform at that other venue this weekend...
Wonder Stage Cast Member A: Haha. It is a bit far away.
Wonder Stage Cast Member B: But we promise to do our best to make the audience smile when we're over there!
Emu: Great! I'll be rooting for all of you!
Wonder Stage Cast Member B: Thank you! Anyway, if you'll excuse us...
Emu: (Alright, that's it for all my on-site jobs! Now I need to go back and meet with Keisuke and Shosuke about...)
???: Ms. Otori...
Emu: Huh?
Emu: What's wrong, Shiratori? Did you forget something?
Shiratori: No, it's not that. I was actually hoping to discuss something with you...
Emu: Discuss something?
Emu: (He seems really nervous... This reminds me of—)
Emu: It's okay...
Emu: You can tell me whatever it is that's on your mind!
Shiratori: Oh...
Shiratori: Thank you. Umm...
Shiratori: The thing is...
Shiratori: I'm thinking about leaving the Wonder Stage.
